:R-HSA-399955  a            obo:GO_0008150 , owl:NamedIndividual ;
        rdfs:comment        "Sema3A, a prototypical semaphorin, acts as a chemorepellent or a chemoattractant for axons by activating a receptor complex comprising neuropilin-1 as the ligand-binding subunit and plexin-A1 as the signal-transducing subunit. Sema3A inhibits cell migration by inhibiting integrin ligand-binding activity." ;
        rdfs:label          "SEMA3A-Plexin repulsion signaling by inhibiting Integrin adhesion" ;
